<paragraph id="8BE836DB5C68FFBBFF38FF72FC7BFF3D" blockId="33.[151,913,151,212]" box="[151,913,151,177]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
<heading id="D0A081B75C68FFBBFF38FF72FC7BFF3D" bold="true" box="[151,913,151,177]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" reason="1">
<emphasis id="B923EAC95C68FFBBFF38FF72FC7BFF3D" bold="true" box="[151,913,151,177]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
<taxonomicName id="4C574D585C68FFBBFF38FF72FD1EFF3D" authority="Machado &amp; Rafael" authorityName="Machado &amp; Rafael" box="[151,756,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Mantispidae" genus="Haematomantispa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amazonica" status="new species">
<emphasis id="B923EAC95C68FFBBFF38FF72FE14FF3D" bold="true" box="[151,510,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Haematomantispa amazonica</emphasis>
Machado &amp; Rafael
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A21057B25C68FFBBFCAEFF72FC7BFF3D" box="[769,913,151,177]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE836DB5C68FFBBFF38FF5FFEDFFF58" blockId="33.[151,913,151,212]" box="[151,309,186,212]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">(Figs. 17–18)</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34D65505C68FFBBFF38FEE0FD0EFEC8" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BE836DB5C68FFBBFF38FEE0FD0EFEC8" blockId="33.[151,1437,261,1855]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
<emphasis id="B923EAC95C68FFBBFF38FEE0FEF2FE93" bold="true" box="[151,280,261,287]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Body almost completely dark reddish brown, pseudopenis extremely long (about 6 times longer than gonarcus median lobe) and hypomere absent.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34D65505C68FFBBFF6AFEAAFB35FA63" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="8BE836DB5C68FFBBFF6AFEAAFEFBFE73" blockId="33.[151,1437,261,1855]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
<emphasis id="B923EAC95C68FFBBFF6AFEAAFE6FFEE5" bold="true" box="[197,389,335,361]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
<typeStatus id="54EC88795C68FFBBFF6AFEAAFED2FEE5" box="[197,312,335,361]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Holotype</typeStatus>
male.
</emphasis>
Head pale yellow at frons, light brown at labrum and clypeus with central longitudinal reddish brown stripe beginning between antennae and ending at labrum, in frontal view (Fig. 17a). Vertex reddish brown, except for two light brown lateral stripes that border eyes (Fig. 17c). Mandible and palpi dark reddish brown, other mouthparts light brown. Antenna dark brown, except for pale yellow scape ventrally (Fig. 17a).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE836DB5C68FFBBFF6AFDEFFC8FFDE3" blockId="33.[151,1437,261,1855]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Pronotum: dark reddish brown, nearly straight in lateral view and completely covered by setae arising directly from it surface (Fig. 17c). Length-width-ratio at maculae: 6.8. Pteronotum: dark reddish brown, pteropleura slightly light (Fig. 17b, c). Scutella without pores</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE836DB5C68FFBBFF6AFD9FFC0AFD53" blockId="33.[151,1437,261,1855]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Foreleg: dark reddish brown, femur and tibia slightly light (Fig. 17d, e). Tarsomere I apex and other tarsomeres yellow. Mid and hindlegs with coxae (Fig. 17b), trochanters, base and apex of femora and tibiae dark reddish brown, other parts pale yellow. Tarsal claws with six teeth.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE836DB5C68FFBBFF6AFD0FFE1CFC33" blockId="33.[151,1437,261,1855]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
Forewing: length: 
<quantity id="4CAF9B3E5C68FFBBFE31FD0FFE16FC88" box="[414,508,746,772]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.7" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" unit="mm" value="9.7">9.7 mm</quantity>
, 7 costal crossveins and 8 veins extended posteriorly from RP. Hyaline, except space between Sc and RA, cell 3M, and area beneath it brown. Cell 1AP apex dark brown. Pterostigma dark reddish brown at apex and yellow at base. Veins brown, except AP2 and bases of AA and AP1 yellow; RA, C, and Sc dark yellow at base, yellow medially, and reddish brown at apex (Fig. 17f). Hindwing: 7 costal crossveins and 9 veins extended posteriorly from RP. Membrane, pterostigma, and veins with color pattern similar to forewing (Fig. 17f).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE836DB5C68FFBBFF6AFC2FFBAEFC68" blockId="33.[151,1437,261,1855]" box="[197,1092,970,996]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Abdomen with sclerites reddish brown and pleura dark brown. Pores absent.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE836DB5C68FFBBFF6AFC15FA94FA83" blockId="33.[151,1437,261,1855]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
Terminalia: ectoproct posterior border rounded. Ventromedial lobe apparently separated from ectoproct, in dorsal view, not sclerotized, with more than 60 stout setae (
<figureCitation id="136C2A5E5C68FFBBFCF4FBF0FC29FBA3" box="[859,963,1045,1071]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="35.[151,255,1880,1904]" captionTargetBox="[215,1370,208,1830]" captionTargetId="figure-83@35.[195,1401,194,1856]" captionTargetPageId="35" captionText="FIGURE 18. Haematomantispa amazonica: male: a, sternite IX, ventral view; b, terminalia, dorsal view; c, gonarcus, dorsal view; d, genitalia, lateral view; e, genitalia, ventral view; female: f, fertilization canal; g, sternite VIII, ventral" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Fig. 18b</figureCitation>
). Sternite IX, subpentagonal with large, medial, rounded lobe at posterior border in ventral view (
<figureCitation id="136C2A5E5C68FFBBFCFDFBDFFC50FBD8" box="[850,954,1082,1108]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="35.[151,255,1880,1904]" captionTargetBox="[215,1370,208,1830]" captionTargetId="figure-83@35.[195,1401,194,1856]" captionTargetPageId="35" captionText="FIGURE 18. Haematomantispa amazonica: male: a, sternite IX, ventral view; b, terminalia, dorsal view; c, gonarcus, dorsal view; d, genitalia, lateral view; e, genitalia, ventral view; female: f, fertilization canal; g, sternite VIII, ventral" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Fig. 18a</figureCitation>
). Gonarcus median lobe long in ventral view (
<figureCitation id="136C2A5E5C68FFBBFF4FFB85FEAFFBF6" box="[224,325,1120,1146]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="35.[151,255,1880,1904]" captionTargetBox="[215,1370,208,1830]" captionTargetId="figure-83@35.[195,1401,194,1856]" captionTargetPageId="35" captionText="FIGURE 18. Haematomantispa amazonica: male: a, sternite IX, ventral view; b, terminalia, dorsal view; c, gonarcus, dorsal view; d, genitalia, lateral view; e, genitalia, ventral view; female: f, fertilization canal; g, sternite VIII, ventral" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Fig. 18c</figureCitation>
). Gonarcus with two small lateral lobes, one small group of scales on dorsal region, and basal extremity wider in lateral view (
<figureCitation id="136C2A5E5C68FFBBFDB5FB60FD56FB13" box="[538,700,1157,1183]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="35.[151,255,1880,1904]" captionTargetBox="[215,1370,208,1830]" captionTargetId="figure-83@35.[195,1401,194,1856]" captionTargetPageId="35" captionText="FIGURE 18. Haematomantispa amazonica: male: a, sternite IX, ventral view; b, terminalia, dorsal view; c, gonarcus, dorsal view; d, genitalia, lateral view; e, genitalia, ventral view; female: f, fertilization canal; g, sternite VIII, ventral" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Fig. 18c, d, e</figureCitation>
). Gonocoxite apex wider in ventral and lateral view and with small scales (
<figureCitation id="136C2A5E5C68FFBBFE9AFB4FFE52FB48" box="[309,440,1194,1220]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="35.[151,255,1880,1904]" captionTargetBox="[215,1370,208,1830]" captionTargetId="figure-83@35.[195,1401,194,1856]" captionTargetPageId="35" captionText="FIGURE 18. Haematomantispa amazonica: male: a, sternite IX, ventral view; b, terminalia, dorsal view; c, gonarcus, dorsal view; d, genitalia, lateral view; e, genitalia, ventral view; female: f, fertilization canal; g, sternite VIII, ventral" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Fig. 18d, e</figureCitation>
). Mediuncus apex bifurcate, in ventral view (
<figureCitation id="136C2A5E5C68FFBBFC7FFB4FFBDCFB48" box="[976,1078,1194,1220]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="35.[151,255,1880,1904]" captionTargetBox="[215,1370,208,1830]" captionTargetId="figure-83@35.[195,1401,194,1856]" captionTargetPageId="35" captionText="FIGURE 18. Haematomantispa amazonica: male: a, sternite IX, ventral view; b, terminalia, dorsal view; c, gonarcus, dorsal view; d, genitalia, lateral view; e, genitalia, ventral view; female: f, fertilization canal; g, sternite VIII, ventral" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Fig. 18e</figureCitation>
). Gonarcal membrane without scales (
<figureCitation id="136C2A5E5C68FFBBFF5FFB35FEBDFB66" box="[240,343,1232,1258]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="35.[151,255,1880,1904]" captionTargetBox="[215,1370,208,1830]" captionTargetId="figure-83@35.[195,1401,194,1856]" captionTargetPageId="35" captionText="FIGURE 18. Haematomantispa amazonica: male: a, sternite IX, ventral view; b, terminalia, dorsal view; c, gonarcus, dorsal view; d, genitalia, lateral view; e, genitalia, ventral view; female: f, fertilization canal; g, sternite VIII, ventral" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Fig. 18e</figureCitation>
). Pseudopenal membrane short (
<figureCitation id="136C2A5E5C68FFBBFD4EFB35FCA2FB66" box="[737,840,1232,1258]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="35.[151,255,1880,1904]" captionTargetBox="[215,1370,208,1830]" captionTargetId="figure-83@35.[195,1401,194,1856]" captionTargetPageId="35" captionText="FIGURE 18. Haematomantispa amazonica: male: a, sternite IX, ventral view; b, terminalia, dorsal view; c, gonarcus, dorsal view; d, genitalia, lateral view; e, genitalia, ventral view; female: f, fertilization canal; g, sternite VIII, ventral" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Fig. 18e</figureCitation>
). Pseudopenis extremely long, more than 6 times longer than gonarcus median lobe, narrow and with apex bent (
<figureCitation id="136C2A5E5C68FFBBFCD4FB10FC16FA83" box="[891,1020,1269,1295]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="35.[151,255,1880,1904]" captionTargetBox="[215,1370,208,1830]" captionTargetId="figure-83@35.[195,1401,194,1856]" captionTargetPageId="35" captionText="FIGURE 18. Haematomantispa amazonica: male: a, sternite IX, ventral view; b, terminalia, dorsal view; c, gonarcus, dorsal view; d, genitalia, lateral view; e, genitalia, ventral view; female: f, fertilization canal; g, sternite VIII, ventral" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Fig. 18d, e</figureCitation>
). Hypomere absent (
<figureCitation id="136C2A5E5C68FFBBFB40FB10FA9BFA83" box="[1263,1393,1269,1295]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="35.[151,255,1880,1904]" captionTargetBox="[215,1370,208,1830]" captionTargetId="figure-83@35.[195,1401,194,1856]" captionTargetPageId="35" captionText="FIGURE 18. Haematomantispa amazonica: male: a, sternite IX, ventral view; b, terminalia, dorsal view; c, gonarcus, dorsal view; d, genitalia, lateral view; e, genitalia, ventral view; female: f, fertilization canal; g, sternite VIII, ventral" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Fig. 18d, e</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE836DB5C68FFBBFF6AFAFFFBD0FAD6" blockId="33.[151,1437,261,1855]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
<emphasis id="B923EAC95C68FFBBFF6AFAFFFE77FAB8" bold="true" box="[197,413,1306,1332]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
<typeStatus id="54EC88795C68FFBBFF6AFAFFFED3FAB8" box="[197,313,1306,1332]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Paratype</typeStatus>
female.
</emphasis>
Similar to male, except for forewing length: 
<quantity id="4CAF9B3E5C68FFBBFC6DFAFFFB8EFAB8" box="[962,1124,1306,1332]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.14" metricValueMax="1.34" metricValueMin="0.94" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" unit="mm" value="11.4" valueMax="13.4" valueMin="9.4">9.4–13.4 mm</quantity>
, and 9–10 veins extended posteriorly from RP. Hindwing with 10–13 veins extended posteriorly from RP.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE836DB5C68FFBBFF6AFA80FB35FA63" blockId="33.[151,1437,261,1855]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
Terminalia: ectoproct as long as or slightly smaller than gonocoxite (
<figureCitation id="136C2A5E5C68FFBBFBB2FA80FB68FAF3" box="[1053,1154,1381,1407]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="35.[151,255,1880,1904]" captionTargetBox="[215,1370,208,1830]" captionTargetId="figure-83@35.[195,1401,194,1856]" captionTargetPageId="35" captionText="FIGURE 18. Haematomantispa amazonica: male: a, sternite IX, ventral view; b, terminalia, dorsal view; c, gonarcus, dorsal view; d, genitalia, lateral view; e, genitalia, ventral view; female: f, fertilization canal; g, sternite VIII, ventral" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Fig. 18i</figureCitation>
). Sternite VIII slightly reduced, but easily seen in lateral and ventral views; in ventral view posterior border rounded with small invagination medially (
<figureCitation id="136C2A5E5C68FFBBFE03FA55FDFFFA46" box="[428,533,1456,1482]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="35.[151,255,1880,1904]" captionTargetBox="[215,1370,208,1830]" captionTargetId="figure-83@35.[195,1401,194,1856]" captionTargetPageId="35" captionText="FIGURE 18. Haematomantispa amazonica: male: a, sternite IX, ventral view; b, terminalia, dorsal view; c, gonarcus, dorsal view; d, genitalia, lateral view; e, genitalia, ventral view; female: f, fertilization canal; g, sternite VIII, ventral" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
Fig. 
<quantity id="4CAF9B3E5C68FFBBFE4BFA55FDFFFA46" box="[484,533,1456,1482]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="1.8" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" unit="g" value="18.0">18g</quantity>
</figureCitation>
). Spermathecal duct coiled with small folds basally (
<figureCitation id="136C2A5E5C68FFBBFB22FA55FB1EFA46" box="[1165,1268,1456,1482]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="35.[151,255,1880,1904]" captionTargetBox="[215,1370,208,1830]" captionTargetId="figure-83@35.[195,1401,194,1856]" captionTargetPageId="35" captionText="FIGURE 18. Haematomantispa amazonica: male: a, sternite IX, ventral view; b, terminalia, dorsal view; c, gonarcus, dorsal view; d, genitalia, lateral view; e, genitalia, ventral view; female: f, fertilization canal; g, sternite VIII, ventral" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Fig. 18h</figureCitation>
), Fertilization canal narrow. Capsule and canal covered by minuscule setae, except for canal base (
<figureCitation id="136C2A5E5C68FFBBFBDFFA30FB38FA63" box="[1136,1234,1493,1519]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="35.[151,255,1880,1904]" captionTargetBox="[215,1370,208,1830]" captionTargetId="figure-83@35.[195,1401,194,1856]" captionTargetPageId="35" captionText="FIGURE 18. Haematomantispa amazonica: male: a, sternite IX, ventral view; b, terminalia, dorsal view; c, gonarcus, dorsal view; d, genitalia, lateral view; e, genitalia, ventral view; female: f, fertilization canal; g, sternite VIII, ventral" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Fig. 18f</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34D65505C68FFBBFF6AFA1FFB6DF943" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BE836DB5C68FFBBFF6AFA1FFCD6F9D3" blockId="33.[151,1437,261,1855]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
<emphasis id="B923EAC95C68FFBBFF6AFA1FFDF3F998" bold="true" box="[197,537,1530,1556]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
Variation, 
<typeStatus id="54EC88795C68FFBBFEFCFA1FFE23F998" box="[339,457,1530,1556]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">paratype</typeStatus>
male.
</emphasis>
Similar to 
<typeStatus id="54EC88795C68FFBBFD05FA1FFCF0F998" box="[682,794,1530,1556]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">holotype</typeStatus>
, except for length-width-ratio at maculae: 6.1–7.1; forewing length 
<quantity id="4CAF9B3E5C68FFBBFEF7F9C5FE1FF9B6" box="[344,501,1568,1594]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.7" metricValueMax="11.3" metricValueMin="8.1" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" unit="mm" value="9.7" valueMax="11.3" valueMin="8.1">8.1–11.3 mm</quantity>
, 8–10 veins extended posteriorly from RP, hindwing with 10–11 veins extended posteriorly from RP, cell 1Cu in hindwing, basally amber.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE836DB5C68FFBBFF6AF98FFB6DF943" blockId="33.[151,1437,261,1855]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
<emphasis id="B923EAC95C68FFBBFF6AF98FFE56F908" bold="true" box="[197,444,1642,1668]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Geographical data.</emphasis>
<materialsCitation id="3B3F3C865C68FFBBFE6AF98FFB6EF943" collectionCode="AM" country="Brazil" county="South America" location="April" municipality="Amazon Region" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" specimenCount="2">
Neotropical, until now with records only from 
<collectingCountry id="F340764B5C68FFBBFBACF98FFBB8F908" box="[1027,1106,1642,1668]" name="Brazil" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Brazil</collectingCountry>
: 
